Package com.icx.domain

Class DomainObject

java.lang.Object
com.icx.common.Common
com.icx.domain.DomainObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<DomainObject>
Direct Known Subclasses:
SqlDomainObject
public abstract class DomainObject extends Common implements Comparable<DomainObject>
Base class for objects managed by a domain controller.

Any specific domain object class must extend this class. Objects managed by specific domain controllers may have a specific base class which extends this class (e.g.: SqlDomainObject for SqlDomainController).

    • canBeDeleted

      public boolean canBeDeleted()
      To override by specific domain class to check if object can be deleted.

      If this method returns false for any object in a deletion process (object itself or any direct or indirect child) no object will be deleted at all.

      Returns:
      true if object can be deleted, false otherwise
